Summary: SSH-2 CTR modes
Difficulty: fun
Class: wish
Priority: medium
Content-type: text/plain
Fixed-in: 2005-04-29

The Internet Draft, draft-ietf-secsh-newmodes-03.txt,
specifies a new symmetric-encryption mode for SSH that doesn't suffer
from the flaws described in ssh2-cbc-weakness.  The relevant ones
(3des-ctr, aes128-ctr, aes192-ctr, aes256-ctr, blowfish-ctr) are now
implemented in PuTTY.
